Durban A 58-year-old man was arrested after dagga and other drugs worth about R1 million was seized from his Durban home on Sunday, police said.A joint operation by the Hawks, eThekwini Crime Intelligence, and Durban Metro Police found 150kg of compressed dagga, benzine, and magic mushrooms after a raid at the home in the New Germany area. Police received information about a man who was dealing in dagga and cannabis oil in the area. The man appeared in Pinetown Magistrate s Court on Monday on a charge of dealing in dagga. The Mercury